# packaging.allowlist — files included in a published/installed artifact.
#
# `make package` ships exactly these paths. Everything else in the repo
# (tests/, .github/, dev-only contracts, caches) is maintainer material and
# stays out of the user's install.
#
# NOTE: the promotion/eval scripts under scripts/ and evals/ DO ship. They are
# part of the Skill's runtime digest surface (workloop_core.SKILL_RUNTIME_SURFACES)
# and the tamper-evidence + governance design depends on their presence. This
# allowlist trims non-runtime material only; it never strips a digested surface.
#
# One path or directory per line. A trailing "/" ships the whole subtree.

SKILL.md
README.md
README.zh-CN.md
LICENSE
packaging.allowlist

.claude-plugin/
agents/
scripts/
references/
assets/

# Runtime eval surfaces (cases, profiles, adapters, policy, registry).
evals/adapters/
evals/profiles/
evals/adapter-contract.md
evals/grader-contract.md
evals/matrix-protocol.md
evals/proposal-contract.md
evals/provider-adapters.md
evals/trigger-cases.json
evals/behavior-cases.json
evals/regression-cases.json
evals/standalone-cases.json
evals/editable-surfaces.json
evals/promotion-policy.json
